~ soloAmigos
do Audio.change_music(Audio.finalAmigos, 0)
do set_background("negroo")
No. Of course not.
What if he rejects me? And then our friendship won’t stay the same?
I can’t risk it, I don’t want to lose someone I hold dear because of a slip up...

After that, days passed and, for some damn reason, what I felt for him didn’t change, moreover, it increased.
I tried to forget any feelings I had about him and every time I was near him I tried focusing on other things that wasn’t him, but, simply put, I couldn’t. It was impossible.
I was in love with Mateo and, for better or for worse, nobody could change that, not even me.

I swear I tried to keep being her friend, but when someone harbors these kind of feelings for a friend, that friendship stops being a pure friendship.
Yes, there is real care, yes, of course, but maybe it’s not the kind that he wants.

With time, I realized that I couldn’t continue like this and I started distancing myself from him, but not for his sake, for mine.
He was always so kind to me, but I wasn’t happy with that kind of relationship. 
I needed more.

I wanted to be his girlfriend, but I never had the courage to tell him anything. 

I wish I would have done it.
I wish I had had the courage that was needed to admit the truth...

